━━━ pi ━━━


Both fixes verified in the sprint doc:

**(a) Q15 async trait object-safety — CLOSED ✅**

Q15 (lines ~504–525) now shows explicit `#[async_trait::async_trait]` on both traits:
```rust
#[async_trait::async_trait]
pub trait WebhookHandler: Send + Sync {
    fn verify(&self, req: &WebhookRequest) -> Result<(), VerifyError>;
    async fn handle(&self, req: WebhookRequest) -> Response;
}

#[async_trait::async_trait]
pub trait WsUpgradeHandler: Send + Sync {
    fn verify_upgrade(&self, req: &Request<Body>) -> Result<(), VerifyError>;
    async fn on_upgrade(&self, ws: WebSocketUpgrade) -> Response;
}
```
The doc comment explicitly explains *why* the macro is needed (concrete expansion to `Pin<Box<dyn Future<Output=Response> + Send + 'a>>`, which is dyn-compatible — unexpanded async fns in traits generate RPITIT opaque futures that are `!Sync`, breaking object-safety). This is the correct fix.

**(b) AC item 2 transport count (7 adapter families) — CLOSED ✅**

Three mentions, all consistent with each other:
- **AC item 2 (line 1001):** "7 transport adapter families operational in code: Telegram, Slack (Socket Mode + Events API webhook), Discord, WhatsApp, Email, Voice, Web."
